tipMessage10: You can debug your code with a specific test case input by right-clicking on any test case and selecting 'Debug with this test case'.
tipMessage2: Holding Ctrl when clicking a run button will force a recompile.
tipMessage3: Holding Alt when clicking a run button will skip compiling.
tipMessage4: You can ask an AI agent to call the #cphNgRunTestcases tool to help you.
tipMessage5: A special judge file can be either source code or an executable.
tipMessage6: You can hide the AC congratulatory GIF in the settings.
tipMessage7: You can hide certain types of test cases in the settings.
tipMessage8: Holding Ctrl when clicking the stop all test cases button will only stop the currently running test case.
tipMessage9: Increase the accuracy of time measurement by checking the Use Wrapper option in the settings.
